        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Leviticus 24</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-20-2" n="20" prev="ADub.III.73.003.023.trl.xml#line-20-1" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="2">‘Command the children of Israel, that they bring to you pure beaten
                            olive oil
                            <milestone unit="page" n="199r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            for the light, to keep the candle burning continually.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="3">Outside the veil of the law, in the tent of meeting,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            Aaron shall prepare it from the evening until morning before the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            always, an eternal statute through your generations.</l>
                        <l n="4">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            He shall arrange the candles on the pure lampstand before
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            the Lord always.</l>
                        <l n="5">And you shall take fine flour and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            bake twelve cakes of it: each cake shall be two-tenth |of a
                            measure|.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="6">And you shall set them in two rows, six
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            cake shall be on a row, on the pure gold table
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            before the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="7">And you shall put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            pure frankincense on |each| row, and it shall be for an incense for the
                            bread, an offering by fire
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            to the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="8">On every Sabbath day, on every Sabbath day, he shall arrange
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            it before the Lord always, <seg type="commented" n="#seg001" />at twilight,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            after burning the incense and after lighting
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            the candles, so that it is hot at the moment it is placed down<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn1"
                                type="noteAnchor" />,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            to make it an eternal statute from the children of Israel.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            And this bread shall be Aaron’s and his sons’, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            they shall eat it that day in the holy place, because it is the holy of holies
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            to him from the offerings by fire of the Lord, an eternal statute.’</l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            And a son of an Israelite woman — and he was a son of an Egyptian man —
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            went out among the children of Israel, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="199v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            the son of the Israelite woman and an Israelite man fought in the
                            camp.</l>
                        <l n="11">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            the Israelite woman’s son specified<ref target="#fn2" type="noteAnchor"
                             /> the name of the Lord and cursed.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            And they brought him to Moses. And his mother’s name was Shelomith,
                            daughter of Dibri,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            of the tribe of Dan.</l>
                        <l n="12">And they put him under guard,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            to determine it for them, <seg type="commented" n="#seg002" />by what
                            kind of death to kill him<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg002" /><ref
                                target="#fn3" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            by the Lord’s command.</l>
                        <l n="13">And the Lord spoke to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            saying,</l>
                        <l n="14">‘Bring out the one who cursed to the outside of the camp
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            and let all who heard him stretch out their hands over his head,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and all the congregation shall stone him.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="15">And you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying, “Any
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            man who curses his God shall bear his punishment.</l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            And the one who specifies<ref target="#fn4" type="noteAnchor" /> the
                            name of the Lord, shall surely be put to death.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            All the congregation shall stone him: as well the stranger as the
                            native: when he specifies<ref target="#fn5" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            the name of the Lord, he shall be put to death.</l>
                        <l n="17">And a man who kills
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            any man’s life shall surely be put to death.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="18">And one who kills an animal’s life shall pay for it:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            a life for a life.</l>
                        <l n="19">And a man who causes a blemish in his fellow:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            as he has done, so shall it be done to him.</l>
                        <l n="20">Fracture
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for tooth:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            as he has caused a blemish in a man, so shall it be done to him,
                            too.</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            And one who kills an animal shall pay for it, and one who kills
                            <milestone unit="page" n="200r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            a man shall be put to death.</l>
                        <l n="22">You shall have one judgement,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            its shall be as well for the stranger, as for the native, because I am
                            the Lord your God.”’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="23">And Moses spoke to the children of Israel. And they brought out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            the one who had cursed to the outside of the camp and stoned him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            with stones. And the children of Israel did as the Lord commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            Moses.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote">An interpretative addition to Lev
                            24:8.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote">A mistranslation based on the confusion
                            of Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">נקב </foreign>
                            ‘to curse, to blaspheme’ (Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיִּקֹּב </foreign>
                            ‘and blasphemed’ in the text) with Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">נקב </foreign>
                            ‘to specify, to mention’ repeated in a number of manuscripts. Cf. Lev
                            24:16.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote">An interpretative addition to Lev
                            24:12.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote">A mistranslation based on the confusion
                            of Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">נקב </foreign>
                            ‘to curse, to blaspheme’ (Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וְנֹקֵב </foreign>
                            ‘and [whoever] blasphemes’ in the text) with Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">נקב </foreign>
                            ‘to specify, to mention’ repeated in a number of manuscripts. Translated
                            correctly in E. Cf. Lev 24:11.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote">A mistranslation based on the confusion
                            of Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">נקב </foreign>
                            ‘to curse, to blaspheme’ (Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">בְּנָקְבוֹ </foreign>
                            ‘when he blasphemes’ in the text) with Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">נקב </foreign>
                            ‘to specify, to mention’ repeated in a number of manuscripts. Translated
                            correctly in E, and R. Cf. Lev 24:11.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
        </body>
